This paper focuses on natural language processing tasks such as text generation and text modification, which are typically studied in the arXiv CS sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as sequence-to-sequence models and attention mechanisms, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval and fact-checking, which are relevant to the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper proposes a method for generating synthetic data, which is related to the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
